The paper discusses clustering analysis in spatial data mining, which is a common topic in the database (cs.DB) and data mining (cs.DM) sub-categories. The use of MapReduce for efficient clustering also suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and parallel algorithms (cs.DS). The comparison of the proposed algorithm with traditional K-Medoids and its scalability on commodity hardware also indicates a potential focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-categories.
